[thinking] **Considering testing and libraries**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about whether tests cover the lifecycle, and it seems like they don’t need to if existing tests already do. Since JDK 25 no longer includes `javax.annotation`, the POM lists that as optional. It makes things deterministic. I'm also wondering about AssertJ; the normal scaffold might include JUnit but probably not AssertJ, which isn't part of the library setup. Also, I need to note that `docker_image` should be none.
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
